The President and First Lady released their 2008 income tax returns, reporting an adjusted gross income of $2,656,902. The majority of their income came from the sale of the President's books. They paid $855,323 in federal income tax and donated $172,050 to 37 different charities, which is about 6.5% of their income. Their largest charitable contributions were $25,000 each to CARE and the United Negro College Fund. They also paid $77,883 in state income taxes in Illinois.